properties.areaDesc: Grays Harbor, WA; Jefferson, WA; Mason, WA; Clallam, WA
properties.headline: Hydrologic Outlook issued January 4 at 4:25AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
A warm front will stall over Western Washington Monday into early
Tuesday. Snow levels will rise in the Olympics up to 5000 feet.
Total rainfall totals for the Monday through Tuesday time frame in
the Olympics could be as high as 7 inches.

It is likely that the Skokomish river in Mason county will flood
Monday night or Tuesday. Other rivers flowing off the Olympics
including but not limited to the Bogachiel river in Clallam county
could flood Tuesday.

Please continue to monitor the latest forecast for the next few
days. Details of potential flooding will change as the situation
evolves.

Latest river forecasts available at
water.weather.gov/ahps2/index.php?wfo=sew

NWSheadline: River flooding possible late Monday into Tuesday along the rivers flowing out of the Olympics
